==English==
===Etymology===
Via French ''[[cesser]]'', from Latin ''[[cessare]]'', frequentative of ''[[cedere]]'', "to go away"

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-iːs|-iːs]]

===Intransitive verb===
'''to cease''' (''present participle'' '''[[ceasing]]''', past tense and past 
participle '''[[ceased]]''')

# (''formal'') To [[stop]].
#:''And with that, his twitching ceased.''
